> Another kind of security level would be to develop kswap alike
> processes.I mean exporting basic process activities in subsidiary kernel
> processes.
One area microkernels actual do well at is having good security partitioning.
You run one copy of the OS for each security boundary and work very hard at
the lowest level microkernel to keep them apart.
